==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spermosphere
<hw>Sper"mo*sphere</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Spermo-</ets> + <ets>sphere</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A mass or ball of cells formed by the
repeated division of a male germinal cell (spermospore), each
constituent cell (spermoblast) of which is converted into a
spermatozoid; a spermatogemma.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spermospore</ent>⟦br⟧
